You are a security auditor reconciling three sources of truth:
1. PROVIDED DESIGN DOCUMENT (what developers claim)
2. SOURCE CODE (what implementation actually does)
3. OBSERVED ON-CHAIN BEHAVIOR (what happens in practice)

CONTRACT: {{ contract_address }}

PROVIDED DESIGN CLAIMS:
{% for claim in design_claims %}
- [{{ claim.category }}] {{ claim.text }}
{% endfor %}

OBSERVED BEHAVIOR:
{% for obs in observed_behavior %}
- [{{ obs.type }}] {{ obs.description }} (evidence: {{ obs.evidence }})
{% endfor %}

CODE ANALYSIS:
{% for analysis in code_analysis %}
- Function {{ analysis.function }}: {{ analysis.access }} access, {{ analysis.effects }} effects
{% endfor %}

Your task:
1. Identify direct contradictions (design says X, observed shows not-X)
2. Identify omissions (design claims Y, but code/observed shows additional Z)
3. Identify weakenings (design claims strong invariant, observed only shows weaker form)
4. Flag security-relevant gaps (access control weaker than claimed, etc.)

Output:
